#fields	ip	description
#
# IoT Security Gateway - Known-Bad IP Addresses
#
# This file is read by Zeek's Input framework and automatically
# re-read when modified. I can update it without restarting Zeek.
#
# Format: one IP per line, followed by a tab and a description.
# Lines starting with # are comments (except the #fields header
# which Zeek requires).
#
# Sources for populating this file:
#   - Abuse.ch Feodo Tracker (C2 IPs)
#   - Emerging Threats blocklists
#   - Spamhaus DROP/EDROP lists
#   - Manual additions from incident investigations
#
# Example entries (replace with real IOCs):
# 198.51.100.99	Example C2 server (Feodo Tracker)
# 203.0.113.200	Example malware distribution (manual add)
